The Economic and Financial Crimes Commission, EFCC, on Thursday, April 25, 2019 again arrested 32 suspected internet fraudsters, popularly known as “Yahoo-Yahoo Boys.” This time the suspects were arrested by the Ibadan Zonal Office of the agency at Liberty Estate, Laderin area of Abeokuta, the Ogun State capital in an early morning sting operation. Tony Orilade, Acting Head, Media and Publicity of the commission who confirmed the arrest to Daily Independent said the suspects are between the ages of 15 and 39 years, and were taken by surprise when EFCC operatives swooped on them at one of their operational base in the estate. It was gathered that fourteen of them claimed to be undergraduates, while 18 others said they are self-employed in various vocations. Their arrest was sequel to a petition detailing their alleged fraudulent activities, including internet fraud through which they obtain illicit funds from unsuspecting victims. Items recovered from them include six exotic cars, laptops, mobile phones, several documents containing false pretences and fetish objects. The commission’s spokesman said the suspects are already helping operatives of the Commission with useful information adding that they will be charged to court as soon as investigations are concluded.